00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:31.000
The other thing was, like, visuals have a limited number per slide. It's easy to overwhelm the audience with a billion things that they need to look at. Oh, and some text.

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:48.000
So the things that I've done for my slide deck at the minute is have, like, one big visual and one small amount of text in big font. Repeat. And be consistent in how those things look.

00:09:48.000 --> 00:10:07.000
And, like, consistent visual design also just helps people kind of, like, just go, it's okay. I don't need to fret that this is a different, you know, animation style or, you know, that things are different styles. It's just, like, you can concentrate on the actual words.

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:29.000
I found that the big images for a slide really helped me remember a presentation too. Like, even my own talk last year about community building, I was thinking, like, what were my four main points? And in my head, I pictured those four, like, the big images on a slide. And then I'm like, okay, I can remember.

