00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:08.000
I like to keep my slides very light. I like to use lots of images, use the 5C color and whatnot.

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:14.000
But when you're meeting leadership, you have a very short amount of time to convey a bunch of information.

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:20.000
So, what I usually do is take all of the images from my slide deck and put them into a sales slip.

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:26.000
It's usually 4 or 5 pages, but it has all of the detail that you're going to cover in the presentation.

00:14:27.000 --> 00:14:31.000
So, when you send out both, now they can see the slide deck.

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:38.000
They can also see all of the detail that you're going to be providing, all of the backup and all of the narrative prior to the meeting.

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:42.000
So then they come in prepared and they can ask really good questions.

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:45.000
For me, it's been pretty successful.

